cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.GR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with learning 3D human dynamics from video using image features and 2D pose annotations. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper presents a framework that can learn a representation of 3D dynamics of humans from video. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is another possible category as the paper discusses the prediction of 3D motion of humans, which is relevant to robotics applications. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper presents a model that can recover the current 3D mesh as well as its 3D past and future motion from a single image. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) is also a possible category as the paper deals with predicting 3D mesh from video, which is relevant to graphics applications.
